The paper deals with the analysis of SINR and throughput scaling in dense urban cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of a dual-slope path loss model suggests that the paper is likely to be related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The focus on urban networks and the use of empirical data may also suggest a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper deals with the scaling of network performance, which could be related to the study of complex systems (cs.SI) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
